[normal]Background[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The New Public Health System
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]P
[normal]HE
[normal]’s purpose
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]invest effectively in prevention and health promotion so that people can live healthier lives and there is reduced demand on health and social care services, as well as on the criminal justice system;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]protect the public by providing a comprehensive range of health protection services;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]commission and deliver safe and effective healthcare services and public health programmes across the whole life course and across care pathways; from prevention through to treatment, from children’s services to mental health and wellbeing, substance misuse services, screening programmes and older people’s services;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]ensure interventions and services are designed and implemented in ways that meet the needs of different groups in society advancing equality of opportunity between protected groups
[normal] 
[normal]and others, and reducing inequalities.
[normal]&#xa0;
